Me, anytime it’s under 45 degrees: “I didn’t move here for this” 🙄 lol

I grew up with the coldest winters in Ohio & I hated it EVERY YEAR! So moving down south I wanted no parts of snow, ice or anything cold (& still don’t). 

Only grateful for the times I get to layer up because fall & winter fashion is slightly better, but still hoping it doesn’t snow on Christmas 🙏🏾 (give me a sunny Christmas day over a snowy one!😊)

Truthfully, this year was a rollercoaster in business, but I’m celebrating every win in from 2022 (& still expecting a few more before the year ends 🙌🏾). 

When I relaunched my brand @prettyperfectstyle_ in 2020, it almost didn’t even happen due to a previous work discrepancy (more on that another time). 

But, I’m so glad it did. At the beginning of the year I told myself I would commit to growing my business every day & I did just that! 

I’m often hard on myself when it comes to the things I want to accomplish, but I’m starting to work on giving myself some flowers 🌸 for all this hard work! 

Cheers to bigger & better success in 2023!

Super excited for 2023! I have a feeling this year will be big 💥

Things Im striving to do more of in 2023:

•Travel

•Anything creative that brings me joy

•Rest

•Make more time to read all the books I buy

•Ask God instead of asking people 

•Practice patience 

•Pray more & worry less

•Prioritize my business while making time for the important people in my life 

•Post more on this page 😩

Cheers to 2023!

IG talk below ⬇️

One of the best things I did was separate my Instagram accounts by topic. I now have 3 😣 lol… (thinking about adding another one but pausing on that for now)

I’m case you were wondering- 

@prettyperfectstyle_ is my jewelry brand

@fashionbizbesties was created because I other fashion e-commerce owners asked questions about how I started & run my business so I wanted a place to give tips & advice. (This is specifically for jewelry designers right now) 

Then, there’s this page which is 90% fashion & sprinkled on with some entrepreneur & hair talk. Basically I post what I want 😊. I feel like this account is mixed up from people that knew me way back in the day, people that joined in during my fashion blogger/stylist days & newer Charlotte friends I’ve gained. So wherever you joined in, this is my journey, hope you enjoy 🙂.

It’s almost been a year since I went all natural so before Women’s History Month ends I’m doing an ode to my natural hair journey. 

1st thing- I love it over here! As a girl who always had my hair straight (always), I’ve been surprised at how much I like my big natural hair & how easy it’s been to maintain (after wash day🤪) 

Things I didn’t know but found out:

I could have 5 different curl patterns in my head

I would soon be going through lots of gel & way more conditioner 

Random ppl would ask to pet my hair like an animal 😳 

I’m grateful to my friends that encouraged me in the beginning when I was about to give up & reach for the flat iron again. (Oh but I’ll still be getting my hair straightened soon so don’t judge me)… 

It took 3 long years to grow my hair out (because I refused to do a big chop) but it was well worth it!

Things I refuse to let go of: 
Faith 
Love 
& this crop top I bust out every spring! It’ll be in heavy rotation now that it’s getting warmer, don’t judge me 😊
Thanks for all the birthday wishes.. & yes, I’m still celebrating 🥳

Every time I take a break from creating content, I miss it so here I am… Working on continuously moving closer to the things that bring me joy. 

Anyways, it’s summertime & I live for a crop top/bandeau/ bralette & wide leg pants situation. ☺️ outfit details ⬇️

Soooo excited for my pop up shop at Nordstrom this month!! 🎉

 I can finally announce that I’ll have a pop up shop for my business @prettyperfectstyle_ at Nordstrom to celebrate Black Business Month on August 19th. 🥳🙌🏾

I started @prettyperfectstyle_ during lockdown & it’s been a fun & eventful ride of ups & downs. Getting the good news of selling in my dream store has made it all worth while! ✨

I’m excited & honored to have a pop up shop On August 19th for my jewelry business through @15percentpledge at the SouthPark Nordstrom in Charlotte. 

Ive been making jewelry for 14 years & have been through quite the business journey (stopped my first jewelry business back in 2016, took 2 years off & started all over again in 2020.) I remember when I first relaunched in 2020, random people gave the worst unsolicited advice. People said it wasn’t smart to start a jewelry business in the middle of lockdown….then I launched & sold out for weeks & weeks in a row & im So glad I didn’t listen to their horrible advice lol. So the lesson is, stop listening to “them”, go after your dream, put in the work & watch God the rest. 😊

If you’re in Charlotte, stop by on the 19th to shop with me in person & Spread the word to any jewelry lovers you know! 😊

August was good to me ☺️

My first pop up shop at Nordstrom was a success 🙌🏾

I was able to represent women owned black businesses in Charlotte at the Beautycounter conference 🙌🏾

I got to spend some much needed time with my parents 😊

And finally got to relax a little. Thanking God in advance that September will be even better! 🙏🏾

Almost 4 years ago I quit my job, packed up my car & moved to Charlotte & 70 degree days in November remind me I made a good decision! 🌞

Since then I’ve grown so much, relaunched my business, and have discovered life as a southerner. 😊

Im so glad I made the move & I’m beyond thankful for all the friends I’ve made & all the opportunities coming my way. ✨

The lesson I continue to learn is that growth doesn’t happen on your comfort zone. I’ll be here in Charlotte until my next big move, wherever that is. ❤️

Number eight on my 2024 goal list 📝 was to get back to content creating because I miss it & it gives me another creative outlet outside of my business. 

I miss creating random outfits, recording them & fighting with the algorithm lol. But I enjoy it So, here we are. ☺️…

These are green themed outfits ( I didn’t realize how much green I had in my wardrobe until I cleaned my closet out last month). 💚

If you want to know where anything is from, ask away in the comments. ⬇️ All jewelry is from my brand @prettyperfectstyle_ 💎
